text: Donna Idelle Axum (January 3, 1942 - November 4, 2018) was an American beauty pageant winner, philanthropist and model. She was newly made Miss Arkansas who was crowned Miss America in 1964. She was born in El Dorado, Arkansas. From 1969 to 1972, she was married to Texas state politician Gus Franklin Mutscher. Axum died on November 4, 2018 in Fort Worth, Texas from complications of Parkinson's disease at the age of 76. ==References== ==Other websites== * Delta Delta Delta Distinguished Alumnae profile * video with transcript Category:1942 births Category:2018 deaths Category:Deaths from Parkinson's disease Category:Disease-related deaths in Texas Category:American models Category:Miss America winners Category:Philanthropists from Arkansas Category:Businesspeople from Arkansas Category:People from El Dorado, Arkansas
